Each traditional energy source has been developed with &amp;#34;significant government engagement,&amp;#34; the report said, citing market control measures for oil and making pipelines available for natural gas distribution.  It added that like oil, gas and coal, solar energy will need to go through a 30-year period of innovation and early adoption before it can &amp;#34;leap&amp;#34; to full market adoption, or reach at least one percent market share.	&#xD;
